Name: total internal ophthalmoplegia
Definition: An anogenital venereal wart that results_in infection located_in skin of anus

Name: obsolete otitis media with effusion
Definition: A non-suppurative otitis media which is a collection of fluid that occurs in the middle ear space as a result of the negative pressure produced by altered Eustachian tube function. This can occur from viral upper respiratory infection or bacterial infection

Name: abnormal pupillary function
Definition: A heart disease that is caused by high blood pressure.
